  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Clinic Assistant",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Description</strong></u></p><p>As a Clinic Assistant, you will be responsible for managing the clinic's day-to-day operations to ensure it is clean, organized and welcoming for patients and medical staff.</p><p><br /></p><p><u><strong>Job Requirement</strong></u></p><p>· Perform general administrative duties assigned by the Clinic Supervisor or Managers, including:</p><p>o Patient registration</p><p>o Record medical history</p><p>o Dispense medication</p><p>o Schedule appointments</p><p>o Reconcile daily monetary transactions</p><p>o Update medical billings & invoices</p><p>o Monthly stock-take of drugs & consumables</p><p>· Assist and chaperone doctors during physical examinations and procedure</p><p>· Prepare and stock examination rooms with necessary supplies. Restock supplies as and when require</p><p>· Communicate effectively with patients to address their concerns</p><p>· Adhere to all clinic policies, procedures, and safety protocols</p><p>· Willing to work shifts (morning / afternoon / night shift)</p><p>· Willing to cover duties in other clinics own by the parent company</p><p><br /></p><p><u><strong>Skills and Knowledge</strong></u></p><p>· Minimum GCE “O” Level or higher; prior healthcare experience is an advantage, but not required as training will be provided</p><p>· Strong interpersonal and communication skills, with a commitment to delivering high-quality patient care</p><p>· Excellent attention to detail and organisational skills</p><p>· Basic knowledge of medical procedures and equipment used in clinical setup</p><p>· Ability to work in a dynamic and fast-paced environment</p><p>· Proficiency in Mandarin is essential for effective communication with Chinese-speaking patients.</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>NOTE: Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted</strong></p>",
